place.name: BYLAUGH
place.gazetteerText: BYLAUGH, a parish in Mitford district, Norfolk; on the river Wensum, 3½ miles ESE of Elmham r. station, and 4½ S of Foulsham. Post Town, Bawdeswell, under Thetford. Acres, 1,546. Real property, £1,701. Pop., 82. Houses, 17. The property is divided between two. The living is a vicarage in the diocese of Norwich. Value, £75. Patron, the Rev. H. Lombe. The church is old but good. (In 1870-72, John Marius Wilson's Imperial Gazetteer of England and Wales)
